## PART 2: COMPLETION ANALYSIS

### Component Status Assessment

| Component | Estimated % | Reality Check |
|-----------|------------|---------------|
| **Core Infrastructure** | 65% | Supervisor + Pipeline work. Orchestrator is copy-pasted LangGraph. Database is functional but thread-unsafe by design. |
| **UI/Desktop** | 15% | PySide6 window is cosmetic. Calls `subprocess.run(python)` to invoke pipeline. No real integration. |
| **Asset Pipeline** | 50% | Downloads work. Validation is mostly checks (`file.exists()`). Blender can be skipped entirely. |
| **Browser Agent** | 5% | BrowserAgent is mentioned in comments but not implemented. DuckDuckGo scraping referenced but not functional. |
| **Memory System** | 25% | Four memory tiers exist (Episodic, Strategy, Procedural, Asset). Recording works. Retrieval is exact-match only. Learning is decorative. |
| **Multi-Agent System** | 30% | BaseAgent exists. GodotAgent exists but doesn't execute independently. Agents are worker wrappers. No true multi-agent collaboration. |
| **Plugin System** | 10% | Skeleton exists. No plugins shipped. No documented plugin API. |
| **Autonomous Learning** | 15% | `discover_and_update_strategies()` groups failures and deletes old strategies. No actual behavioral adaptation. |
| **Self-Healing** | 20% | Retry logic (max 3 attempts). Supervisor handles some failures. Fallback LLM templates exist. No root-cause analysis. |
| **Game Generation** | 25% | Can generate basic FPS scenes. Static layout assembly only. No procedural generation. No gameplay mechanics beyond fallback GDScript stubs. |
| **Linux Distro Components** | 0% | No mention. Outside scope. |
| **Production Readiness** | 10% | Config-dependent. Requires manual Godot/Blender setup. Authentication missing. Error handling is incomplete. |

### Completion Percentages

**Engineering Completion: 40%**
- Core orchestration works.
- Workers can execute.
- Database is usable (single-threaded).
- Config system is reasonable.
- **Missing**: distributed coordination, monitoring, real error recovery.

**Product Completion: 15%**
- Can generate basic scenes on successful runs.
- Desktop UI is non-functional (cosmetic).
- No user-facing docs or examples.
- No real asset curation.
- Memory system doesn't influence behavior.

**Final Vision Completion: 8%**
- Multi-agent autonomy: **not present** (agents are thin wrappers).
- Self-improvement: **not present** (memory is read-only for retrieval).
- Procedural generation: **not present** (static templates only).
- Cloud deployment: **skeletal** (FTP-based, untested).
- Game mechanics synthesis: **not present** (fallback templates only).

