## PART 5: RUNTIME ANALYSIS

### Actual Execution Path

```
Prompt
  ↓
AppContext.__init__() [wires singletons]
  ↓
Pipeline.execute(job) [LINEAR by default, DAG optional]
  ├─→ internet_worker.run(job, state)
  │    └─→ Hits: Kenney API mock OR hardcoded test assets
  │    └─→ Downloads 1-4 assets (real ZIP files)
  │    └─→ Returns: assets[] with file_path, format, etc.
  │
  ├─→ analysis_worker.run(job, state)
  │    └─→ Checks asset format (FBX, GLB, OBJ, etc.)
  │    └─→ Reads FBX headers to count meshes (heuristic)
  │    └─→ Returns: normalized_assets[] with metadata
  │
  ├─→ blender_worker.run(job, state)
  │    ├─→ IF blender binary available:
  │    │    └─→ Generates Python script → runs `blender --background --python`
  │    │    └─→ Script imports assets, applies materials, exports FBX
  │    │    └─→ May TIMEOUT (600s) or CRASH
  │    │    └─→ On failure: writes ASCII FBX stub (FAKE)
  │    └─→ ELSE:
  │         └─→ Deterministic grid layout (FAKE)
  │         └─→ Writes ASCII FBX stub (FAKE)
  │
  ├─→ godot_worker.run(job, state)
  │    ├─→ Creates project.godot + Scenes/main.tscn
  │    ├─→ Runs: godot --headless --path <project> --import
  │    │    └─→ Imports FBX (or ASCII stub) into Godot
  │    ├─→ IF scene loads: returns success
  │    └─→ ELSE: may launch editor (Windows-specific) or return error
  │
  ├─→ code_worker.run(job, state)
  │    ├─→ Prompt LLM: "Write GDScript for <objective>"
  │    ├─→ IF LLM succeeds: compile with godot --headless --check-only
  │    ├─→ IF compilation fails: retry up to 3x with error feedback
  │    └─→ ELSE (all providers fail): use hardcoded fallback template
  │
  ├─→ validation_worker.run(job, state)
  │    └─→ Checks: assets exist, scene.tscn exists, project.godot exists
  │    └─→ Checks: import files (.fbx.import) exist
  │    └─→ Checks: syntax is valid (regex check for [gd_scene tag)
  │    └─→ DOES NOT: actually load scene in Godot runtime
  │    └─→ Returns: PASS if all file checks pass
  │
  └─→ deploy_worker.run(job, state) [OPTIONAL, usually skipped]
       └─→ Builds HTML5 export (if configured)
       └─→ FTP uploads to server (untested)
```

### Systems Actually Executed
- ✓ **Asset Search** (real API + mock fallback)
- ✓ **Analysis** (format parsing + heuristics)
- ✗ **Blender** (fallback to ASCII stub if unavailable)
- ✓ **Godot** (headless import + scene generation)
- ✗ **Code** (fallback templates if LLM fails)
- ✗ **Validation** (only checks files, not runtime)
- ✗ **Deploy** (untested, requires credentials)

### Systems Only Architecturally Present
- **Multi-Agent DAG** (orchestrator supports it; pipeline doesn't use it)
- **Inter-Agent Communication** (event bus exists; agents don't listen)
- **Autonomous Learning** (memory records but doesn't change behavior)
- **Self-Healing** (retry logic only; no root-cause analysis)

