## PART 6: TECHNICAL DEBT

### Critical Issues

| Issue | Severity | Impact |
|-------|----------|--------|
| **Database thread safety** | **CRITICAL** | Single connection pooled across threads. SQLite "database is locked" crashes in concurrent scenarios. Supervisor spawns ThreadPoolExecutor but DB.execute() is not thread-safe. |
| **Blender/Godot binary misconfigurations** | **CRITICAL** | If binaries are wrong paths, workers fail silently and fall back to stubs. No binary health check at startup. |
| **Mock FBX generation** | **CRITICAL** | ASCII FBX stub is 200 lines of hardcoded geometry. Not valid for complex assets. Godot import may fail. No error propagation. |
| **Memory system doesn't influence planning** | **CRITICAL** | Memories are recorded but Supervisor planning doesn't consult them. Asset reuse is not implemented. |
| **No transaction rollback** | **CRITICAL** | If pipeline fails mid-execution, checkpoint is saved but partial assets remain. Cleanup is manual. |
| **Orchestrator is deprecated copy-paste** | **CRITICAL** | `GraphOrchestrator.run()` marked as deprecated. Sequential path only. DAG scheduling has thread-safety bugs (W5 comment in code). |
| **Checkpoint manager uses relative paths** | **HIGH** | `CheckpointManager._get_path()` defaults to `Path(".")`. If CWD changes, checkpoints are lost. (W6 issue noted in code.) |
| **No authentication** | **HIGH** | FastAPI server has no API keys, no user isolation. FTP credentials hardcoded in config. |
| **VisionSubsystem missing** | **HIGH** | validation_worker imports it but file doesn't exist. Silent ImportError. |
| **No observability** | **HIGH** | Event bus exists but dashboard never subscribes. No metrics exported. No alerting. |

### Architectural Problems

| Problem | Details |
|---------|---------|
| **Tight Coupling: Workers ↔ Database** | Every worker imports Database, making testing hard. Mock database required for unit tests. |
| **Circular Dependencies** | `main.py` wires 30+ components. If any fails, entire context fails. No graceful degradation. |
| **God Object: AppContext** | Holds all singletons. 150+ lines of __init__. No separation of concerns. |
| **Aspirational Agents** | BaseAgent exists but workers execute tasks directly. Agents are never instantiated in production. Multi-agent DAG is architectural fiction. |
| **Memory System Ignored** | Four memory subsystems exist but Supervisor doesn't consult them. Episodic memory is never used for reuse detection. |
| **Pipeline Linear by Default** | DAG support exists but pipeline.py uses sequential routing. Parallel execution requires manual opt-in. |
| **No Versioning** | AppContext wires deprecated components alongside new ones. Migration path is unclear. |

### Scaling Issues

| Issue | Limit |
|-------|-------|
| **Concurrent jobs** | Supervisor.max_concurrent_jobs defaults to 2. Database is single-connection. Threading will cause "database is locked" errors. |
| **Asset caching** | No cache eviction. Cache directory grows unbounded. 8 test assets = 200MB+ after format conversions. |
| **Memory growth** | Episodic memory accumulates forever. No archival. After 1000 jobs, queries slow. |
| **Blender/Godot process pool** | Each job spawns one Blender + one Godot process. No pooling. 10 concurrent jobs = 10 Blender + 10 Godot = >80GB RAM. |
| **Checkpoint disk usage** | Each checkpoint is full JSON serialization of state. Large asset lists = checkpoint files >100MB. |

### Maintainability Risks

| Risk | Probability |
|------|-------------|
| **Broke inheritance chain** | BaseWorker.recover() never called in normal flow. Exception handling is global try-catch. |
| **Inconsistent error handling** | Some workers raise WorkerError; others return WorkerResult(FAILED). No standard. |
| **Type hints incomplete** | Many Dict[str, Any], List. IDE autocomplete broken. |
| **Tests mock too much** | Unit tests create fake workers, fake databases. Don't catch real failures. |
| **Config hell** | Three JSON files (config.json, providers.json, templates.json). No validation schema. |

