## PART 7: PRODUCTION BLOCKERS

### Must Fix Before Any Deployment

| Blocker | Current Status | Effort |
|---------|---|---|
| **Authentication** | None. No API keys, no user isolation. | 3-5 days |
| **Database persistence** | SQLite single-connection. Crashes under load. | 2-3 days (switch to PostgreSQL + connection pooling) |
| **Binary availability** | Godot/Blender paths are config-dependent. No health checks at startup. | 1 day |
| **Error recovery** | Retry logic exists but doesn't solve problems. If asset download fails, no fallback. | 3-5 days |
| **Observability** | Event bus exists but dashboard is dead. No logs, metrics, or alerts. | 5-7 days |
| **Documentation** | README is vague. No API docs. Config.json has no schema. No runbook. | 3-4 days |

### High-Risk Scenarios

| Scenario | Outcome |
|----------|---------|
| **Godot binary missing** | Silent fallback to stub validation. User gets a "valid" scene that loads blank. |
| **OOM (>90% RAM)** | Resource gate pauses 15s then proceeds anyway. Process crashes. |
| **Network timeout during download** | Retry 3x then fail. Asset not found error. No fallback asset. |
| **Blender FBX export timeout** | ASCII stub written (FAKE geometry). Godot imports it successfully. User sees blank scene. |
| **Two jobs same asset** | Both download, both cache separately. 2x disk usage, 2x network time. No deduplication. |
| **Config paths wrong** | Workers fail silently. Fallback to stubs. Pipeline completes "successfully" but generates fake scenes. |
| **Database corruption** | No recovery. Manual intervention required. |

