## PART 13: FINAL REPORT

### Scoring Breakdown

| Dimension | Score | Justification |
|-----------|-------|---|
| **Architecture** | 6/10 | Good orchestration. Poor separation of concerns. Circular dependencies. Agents are unused. |
| **Code Quality** | 4/10 | Decent patterns. Type hints missing. Tests don't cover integration. Mock/stub problem understated in code. |
| **Production Readiness** | 2/10 | No auth. DB thread-unsafe. No observability. Fallback to mocks masks failures. Config-dependent. |
| **Innovation** | 5/10 | Multi-tier memory is clever. Graph orchestrator is copy-paste. Asset normalization pipeline is solid. Self-correction loops are good (but incomplete). |
| **Maintainability** | 3/10 | God object (AppContext). Circular wiring. Unused agents. Tests mock too much. Config hell. |
| **Reliability** | 3/10 | Happy path works. Error paths have fallback stubs. Unclear what's real vs. fake. No integration testing. |

### Overall Scores

| Metric | Score |
|--------|-------|
| **Architecture** | 6.0/10 |
| **Code Quality** | 4.0/10 |
| **Production Readiness** | 2.0/10 |
| **Innovation** | 5.0/10 |
| **Maintainability** | 3.0/10 |
| **Reliability** | 3.0/10 |
| **AVERAGE** | **3.8 / 10** |

